ce:section.ce:para:
The first term (E

                           BS
                        ) is the “band structure term” obtained from the sum of all occupied eigenstates, which are expressed in a minimal basis of pseudoatomic orbitals generated from an all-electron DFT calculation for each atom. The second term (E

                           rep
                        ) corresponds to the repulsive potentials approximated as a sum of two-body interactions. These two terms correspond to the non-self-consistent DFTB method [36]. The final term (E
                        2nd
                        ) represents the energy contribution caused by density fluctuations (self-consistent charge (SCC) approximation). The SCC-DFTB offers several advantages including short calculation time, free of basis set superposition error (BSSE), and reliable description of dispersions and weak interactions leading to qualitative agreement with experimental observations [37–39]. The adsorption behavior of gas molecule on OH-GQD has been thus studied by the SCC-DFTB method to explain the related gas-sensing mechanisms. All SCC-DFTB calculations were performed using the DFTB+ code [40].
